<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[192,1440,1059,1179]" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,315,1059,1083]" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2014" box="[330,532,1059,1083]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[330,532,1059,1083]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">Glaresis limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all other known species in this subgroup by the dull, dense, strongly rugose clypeal surface and medioanterior portion of frons; widely spaced pronotal carinae; and smooth elytral surface completely lacking microreticulation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[192,1440,1059,1179]" box="[240,633,1155,1179]" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">
The 
<typeStatus box="[294,399,1155,1179]" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">holotype</typeStatus>
is a unique female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="51" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="52.[192,1440,1219,1275]" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1219,1243]" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2014" box="[708,801,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Glaresidae" genus="Glaresis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbata">
<emphasis box="[708,801,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="51">limbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning border, referring to the well defined, lateral flange of the metatibia.
</paragraph>
